OneRepublic has long been credited with songs that blend the energy of pop with the nuance of alternative rock. This dynamic ensemble, formed in 2002, released their first album, Dreaming Out Loud, in 2007.

Currently comprised of six individuals, the band’s lineup features Ryan Tedder as the lead vocalist, Zach Filkins and Drew Brown on guitars, Brian Willett on piano, Brent Kutzle on cello, and Eddier Fisher on drums.

With its retro touch, this catchy Christmas track’s sing along, karaoke-ready, visualizer invites us to get into the season spirit.

About OneRepublic:

Grammy® nominated OneRepublic, is comprised of singer/songwriter and lead vocalist Ryan Tedder, guitarists Zach Filkins and Drew Brown, keys Brian Willett, bassist and cellist Brent Kutzle, and drummer Eddie Fisher. The band released their debut set Dreaming Out Loud in 2007. The release included the 20mm selling smash single “Apologize,” which shattered digital sales and airplay records worldwide and received a Grammy nomination. The band’s sophomore album, 2009’s Waking Up, produced the hit singles “All the Right Moves,” “Secrets” and “Good Life.” The certified-platinum album Native followed in 2013, featuring the No.1 hit and 41 million selling single “Counting Stars.” OneRepublic released Oh My My, their fourth full-length album in 2016. The toughest thing about being a rock star? Being away from their newborn sons, say OneRepublic frontman Ryan Tedder and guitarist Zach Filkins.

“It’s hard,” says Filkins, who welcomed his first child, son Leighton, with wife Lindsay in June. “You reach a point where the more you see them [in online video chats], the more you want to go home.”

Adds frontman Tedder, who welcomed son Copeland Cruz with wife Genevieve 11 weeks ago: “We try to cap our time away at three weeks, whereas in the past we’d do six weeks. You don’t understand until you have a...

OneRepublic's frontman Ryan Tedder is officially a first time dad. Tedder, the man behind Leona Lewis' "Bleeding Love" and Beyonce Knowles' "Halo" hits, welcomed his son with wife Genevieve on Monday afternoon, August 2, E! Online reported.

The tot wasn't actually scheduled to be out until August 8. While Tedder's rep has not yet released details about the newly-born baby boy including his name, a source told the site, "Mom and baby are doing well and the couple is very happy."

Tedder seemed ready for fatherhood as he recently claimed he has studied parenting books prior to his son's arrival. He stated, "I've done my homework. So hopefully I can handle it." Tedder could also turn for advice to his bandmate guitarist Zach Filkins and his wife Lindsay, who recently became parents to little Leighton Zachary.

Ryan Tedder, the man behind Leona Lewis' "Bleeding Love" and Beyonce Knowles' "Halo" hits, is set to become a first-time father in August. The singer/songwriter and OneRepublic's frontman has revealed his wife Genevieve is a month away from her due date, and he's very excited. He tells People, "I'm going to be a dad for the first time. I'm extremely excited and looking forward to it. We are having a boy. (Genevieve)'s due in about four weeks."

And Tedder has been busy studying parenting books to prepare him for the impending arrival. He adds, "I've done my homework. So hopefully I can handle it." The star will be able to turn to his bandmates for support and guidance - OneRepublic's lead guitarist Zach Filkins and his wife Lindsay recently became parents to little Leighton Zachary.

One Republic frontman Ryan Tedder is used to the screams of fans but will soon be adjusting to cries of a different kind — he and wife Genevieve are expecting their first child in early August.

“Yes, it’s true. I’m going to be a dad for the first time,” Tedder, 31, confirms to People. “I’m extremely excited and looking forward to it.”

“We are having a boy,” the singer/songwriter revealed, smiling. “[Genevieve]‘s due in about four weeks.”

OneRepublic's live performance scene is highlighted in a newly-premiered music video for their single "Marchin On". The band's members Ryan Tedder, Zach Filkins, Brent Kutzle, Drew Brown and Eddie Fisher are featured in individual scenes in addition to gathering in one shot.

"Marchin On" is one of the songs appearing in OneRepublic's second studio album "Waking Up" which has been released since November 2009. Produced and written by Ryan, this track is chosen to be the anthem for German team that will compete in 2010 FIFA World Cup.

Ryan Tedder and his bandmates are currently on tour, going to spend almost the whole June in Europe for a series of concerts in the continent to promote "Waking Up". Afterwards, they will return Stateside and perform in North America and Canada before flying back across the pond for one more time. More detailed info about their upcoming show can be found on their official site.
